-- Bank Rakyat, Pakuwon, Telekomunikasi: Indonesia Equity Preview
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-01-19T01:39:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/bank-rakyat-pakuwon-telekomunikasi-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 0.6 percent to 3,978.13.  PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BBRI)  : Net income at the
nation’s second-biggest bank by market value may have risen last
year to 11.4 trillion rupiah ($1.3 billion), Corporate Secretary
Muhamad Ali said yesterday. Bank Rakyat advanced 1.4 percent to
7,050 rupiah.  PT Pakuwon Jati (PWON)  : The property developer may seek
as much as 1 trillion rupiah of loans to refinance debt,  Bisnis
Indonesia  reported, citing Finance Director Minarto Basuki.
Pakuwon fell 1.3 percent to 790 rupiah.  PT Telekomunikasi Indonesia (TLKM)  : Indonesia’s biggest
telephone company expects revenue to rise 5 percent to 6 percent
this year compared with 2011 bolstered by growth in its data and
cellular business, Kontan reported, citing Finance Director
Sudiro Asno. Telkom, as the company is also known, was unchanged
at 7,000 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
